A Malindi businessman is celebrating Christmas in pain after police officers enforcing the ongoing curfew allegedly manhandled him, breaking his arm.
Mr Zackayo Kaibunga was accused of being out after 10pm, when the curfew starts. He had to seek treatment from a private hospital in Malindi following the beating.



